title.narrative: LESTARI Project - Sustainable Landscapes and Biodiversity Flagship

description.narrative: (Indonesia): .LESTARI is a partnership between the GOI and USAID that aims to reduce greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions and conserve biodiversity in carbon rich and biologically significant forest and mangrove ecosystems. At least 30 million people depend directly on Indonesia's forests for their livelihoods. Indonesia's deforestation rates ranking among the highest in the world and their biodiversity continues to be under serious threat. A history of weak governance combined with opportunistic private sector actors has created unsustainable natural resource exploitation. LESTARI addresses these issues in six strategic landscapes in the provinces of Aceh, Central Kalimantan, and Papua. It applies a landscape-based approach to conserve biodiversity and reduce GHG emissions, integrating forest and peatland conservation with low emissions development. It is achieved through strengthening land use governance, enhanced protected areas management and protection of key species (elephant, tiger, orangutan), sustainable private sector and industry practices, and expanded constituencies for conservation among various stakeholders. Specifically, orangutan conservation will continue to ensure the $2.5 million earmark goes towards practical and sustainable solutions. USAID continues rehabilitation and release of captive orangutans into a national park. LESTARI with and through stakeholders is a catalyst for self-sufficient, transparent, and sustainable solutions to natural resource governance challenges. LESTARI contributes to the U.S. Mission objective of supporting Indonesia's greater global and regional role promoting democratic values, rule of law, and protecting the environment, public health, and other shared priorities. Effective natural resource management, including the protection of its biodiversity, by the government of Indonesia also positively contributes to its long-term economic prosperity and is a core component of Indonesia's journey to self-reliance..
